**/run-artifact-client/
verification/neoforge-artifact-client/run/
verification/evidence/**
# Durable post-v1 ordered client-flow reports are explicit evidence, not disposable run output.
!verification/evidence/fabric-26.2-flow-main-menu-20260714T210730Z.json
!verification/evidence/fabric-26.2-flow-world-20260714T210800Z.json
!verification/evidence/fabric-26.2-flow-shutdown-20260714T210816Z.json
!verification/evidence/forge-1.20.1-flow-main-menu-20260714T215732Z.json
!verification/evidence/forge-1.20.1-flow-world-20260714T215815Z.json
!verification/evidence/forge-1.20.1-flow-shutdown-20260714T215827Z.json
# Phase 1 judgment report and benchmark aggregate summaries are durable deliverables, not
# disposable per-run output (per-seed logs/reports under timestamped subfolders stay ignored).
#
# A file-level negation cannot resurrect a file whose parent directory is still excluded by the
# blanket `verification/evidence/**` above - git will not descend into an ignored directory to
# check finer per-file rules unless the directory itself is also explicitly un-ignored. Without
# the directory-level negation below, `!verification/evidence/*/aggregate.json` silently matched
# nothing: confirmed live (`git check-ignore -v`) that every prior "official"/rescoring
# aggregate.json, going back to the first ones this convention comment describes, was never
# actually tracked despite this file's own stated intent.
!verification/evidence/other-repos-intelligence-layer-judgment-2026-07-17.md
# Un-ignore each per-run subdirectory just far enough for git to traverse into it, then re-ignore
# everything inside it again except the one durable file - otherwise the directory-level negation
# above would also resurrect every disposable per-seed log/report it was supposed to exclude.
!verification/evidence/*/
verification/evidence/*/*
!verification/evidence/*/aggregate.json
**/build/
**/.gradle/
**/run/
**/runs/
**/logs/
libraries/
*.jar.log
verification/curseforge-profiles/*.zip
verification/curseforge-profiles/*/overrides/

# Local comparison repositories; never include third-party source in Lodestone uploads.
other-repos/

# Build/IDE/crash artifacts; never meaningful to commit.
**/bin/
**/.eclipse/
.cache/
.serena/
hs_err_pid*.log
replay_pid*.log

# In-progress local demo capture sessions; curated output is published separately.
demo-videos/
